    "narrative": "The **Austin Waves** offense is primed for a high-ceiling performance today, anchored by **Gunnar Henderson** and **Kyle Tucker**. **Gunnar Henderson** commands our highest score (83.29) as he draws a favorable matchup against R. Nelson; the combination of a significant park boost (+16%) and a favorable wind-out condition makes him our primary anchor. **Kyle Tucker** follows closely (72.71) against the southpaw David Peterson. While the platoon edge for **Kyle Tucker** is neutral, his elite xwOBA of .372 and high spot in the order ensure he remains an auto-start. We are also monitoring **Luis Robert Jr.** (61.23) closely; while he faces a tough arm in Justin Wrobleski, the high stolen base potential\u2014fueled by a slow delivery to the plate\u2014gives him added value in our scarce SB category.\n\nStrategic depth remains a focus as we navigate several \"Lineup Pending\" designations. **Josh Jung** (60.22) is a notable riser today, benefiting from a massive +15% SP skill boost despite facing Luis Severino, though his low spot in the batting order suppresses an otherwise elite projection. The most difficult bench decision involved **Brady House**, whose 42.69 score was the highest of our non-starters. Ultimately, the optimizer opted for **Jacob Wilson** (46.85) in the UTIL slot; despite a difficult matchup against Nathan Eovaldi, **Jacob Wilson** possesses a stronger park factor and a more advantageous position in the batting order compared to **Brady House**, who was penalized for facing the formidable Paul Skenes and an elite defensive catcher. \n\nRisk management is central to today\u2019s rotation. Owners should note that the high scores for **Drake Baldwin**, **Liam Hicks**, **Nolan Schanuel**, **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.**, **Jorge Polanco**, **Josh Jung**, **Josh Lowe**, **Andy Pages**, **Luis Robert Jr.**, **Kyle Tucker**, and **Jacob Wilson** are contingent on confirmed lineups; any unexpected drop in the batting order will necessitate a reassessment of their daily efficiency. Furthermore, we are proceeding with caution against Skenes, which accounts for the marginal scores for **Luis Garc\u00eda Jr.** and **Nasim Nunez**. While **Vladimir Guerrero Jr.** and **Jordan Westburg** are unavailable today due to scheduling and injury respectively, our remaining depth provides sufficient coverage to chase categories without overextending our game caps.",
